<br>
It could be a pressure and/or speed thing if you simply mean your lines come out inconsistent and also a paper issue.  Some papers are very bad for inking.<br>
<br>
Or are you talking about when you use a ruler or straightedge and this blob just appears?  What happens there is that the ink gets trapped under the straightedge causing a blotch.  There are a few ways to correct that.  One is to get a ruler with an inking edge, which can be found in the drafting supplies section at art stores and office supply stores.  An inking edge is raised a little off the paper to prevent trapping the ink.  Some people tape dimes along the bottom of their straight edge to raise it off the paper, and others hold their straight edge at a 45 degree angle.  Getting a rulers and traingles with inking edges is the easiest way to go.  Sorry if you already know this...trying to guess what you mean.<br>
